<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8307239>
    dc:description "FIGURE 32. Pauridia ovata. A, whole plant; B, leaf in transverse section; C, scape apex, bract and pedicel: D, outer stamen in dorsal view; E, two inner stamens in dorsal and lateral views on left and right respectively; F, style and stigma branches; G, ovary in transverse section; H, capsule; I, seed. Scale bar A = 20 mm; B = 3 mm; C–F = 2 mm; G = 3 mm; H = 0.35 mm. Drawn by Nicci Page- Cairns from Snijman 2047 (NBG!)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8307239/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8307241>
    dc:description "FIGURE 33. Distribution maps for A, Pauridia ovata from Western Cape; B, P. gracilipes subsp. gracilipes (dots) from Northern and Western Cape; P.gracilipes subsp. speciosa (triangles) from Northern Cape, South Africa." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8307241/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

